                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout><p>Text is generally well centred and lines 1 and 4 take up the whole of the available horizontal space. Line 3 has very evidently been added by another hand, probably at a later date.</p>
                                    <rs ana="#execution.chiselled" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1">chiselled</rs>
                                    <damage/>
                                </layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote><p>Text is mostly complete, but for the top half of the first line. The letters in lines 1, 2 and 4 are tall, neat and seriffed, with triangular interpuncts. Line 3 is less assured: the text is freer, less regular, and the letters are less symmetrical than the rest.</p>
